ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A fairly heavy course in terms of workload; an interesting field but not necessarily strongly tied in with the broader conceptual issues afoot. Recommended for students prepared to work consistently who have an interest in textual, generic and tropological issues in the Baroque.
This was an excellent course on a well-framed and intriguing subject, and I would highly recommend it to other students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: After this course I fell more prepare to develop a research project, which will contribute for my dissertation.

Broadened understanding of the period and definitely improved knowledge of the relevant repertoire. Illustrated some interesting approaches and difficulties of approach in a field that interests me; may be of use in further research but unlikely to affect dissertation.
